      • generateExceptionForError

        private static PrismException generateExceptionForError()
        Generate the proper exception for an error from the native layer. Gets the error message and returns the corresponding exception, i.e., if the message contains "not supported" then a PrismNotSupportedException is returned, otherwise a plain PrismException.

      • Reachability

        public static JDDNode Reachability(JDDNode trans01,
                                   JDDVars rows,
                                   JDDVars cols,
                                   JDDNode start)
        Reachability computation, computes the set Post*(start).
        Note: For non-deterministic models, take the transition matrix with the non-deterministic choices removed, i.e., getTransReln().
        [ REFS: result, DEREFS: none ]
        Parameters:
        trans01 - the 0/1-transition matrix of the model (over rows, cols)
        rows - the row variables of the model
        cols - the col variables of the model
        start - the starting states for the reachability computation
        Returns:
        the set of states that can be reached from start

        PCTL until probability 1 precomputation (probabilistic/dtmc)
        [ REFS: result, DEREFS: none ]
        Parameters:
        trans01 - the 0/1-transition matrix of the DTMC (trans01, over rows, cols)
        reach - the set of reachable states in the DTMC
        rows - the row variables of the model
        cols - the col variables of the model
        b1 - the set of b1 states (needs to be contained in reach)
        b2 - the set of b2 states (needs to be contained in reach)
        no - the set of states with 'P[ b1 U b2 ] = 0'
        Returns:
        the set of states with 'P[ b1 U b2 ] = 1'

        PCTL until probability 1 precomputation - there exists (nondeterministic/mdp).
        [ REFS: result, DEREFS: none ]
        Parameters:
        trans01 - the 0/1-transition matrix of the MDP (trans01, over rows, cols, nd)
        reach - the set of reachable states in the MDP
        rows - the row variables of the model
        cols - the col variables of the model
        nd - the nondeterministic choice variables of the model
        b1 - the set of b1 states (needs to be contained in reach)
        b2 - the set of b2 states (needs to be contained in reach)
        no - the set of states with 'for all strategies P[ b1 U b2 ] = 0' (needs to be contained in reach)
        Returns:
        the set of states with 'there exists a strategy with P[ b1 U b2 ] = 1'
